00:01:39.260 --> 00:01:42.400
And before I jump into
some of the new stuff,

00:01:42.400 --> 00:01:45.120
let me put it into
perspective a bit.

00:01:45.120 --> 00:01:49.420
This is actually a computer game
I wrote 40 years ago this year.

00:01:49.420 --> 00:01:52.900
The code's on the left, and the
actual game input and output

00:01:52.900 --> 00:01:54.060
is on the right.

00:01:54.060 --> 00:01:57.350
At that point, when we
were doing computer games,

00:01:57.350 --> 00:02:00.400
we basically had sort of
glorified electric typewriters,

00:02:00.400 --> 00:02:02.960
and that was our
input and output.

00:02:02.960 --> 00:02:05.810
On this particular game, you
had a list of numerical commands

00:02:05.810 --> 00:02:07.570
you would type in.

00:02:07.570 --> 00:02:10.020
Just a year or two
after that came out,

00:02:10.020 --> 00:02:12.400
I saw my first
video screen and got

00:02:12.400 --> 00:02:14.601
to code with something
that actually controlled

00:02:14.601 --> 00:02:15.600
the video on the screen.

00:02:15.600 --> 00:02:17.250
And it was a revelation for me.

00:02:17.250 --> 00:02:20.390
And of course, right around that
time, as video and computers

00:02:20.390 --> 00:02:22.980
were coming together, it made
some of the first video games

00:02:22.980 --> 00:02:24.040
possible.

00:02:24.040 --> 00:02:25.640
And those kinds of
combinations, we've

00:02:25.640 --> 00:02:27.098
actually become
kind of used to it.

00:02:27.098 --> 00:02:29.280
But every few years there's
some new dramatic mix

00:02:29.280 --> 00:02:31.670
of new technologies
that can come together

00:02:31.670 --> 00:02:32.970
in these great ways.

00:02:32.970 --> 00:02:36.824
For example, we had CD-ROMs
and a higher color resolution

00:02:36.824 --> 00:02:38.490
that enabled the kind
of modern graphics

00:02:38.490 --> 00:02:39.760
that we're used to now.

00:02:39.760 --> 00:02:42.000
Or modems and
server-based architecture

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:45.790
that made MMOs and a lot of
the online games possible.

00:02:45.790 --> 00:02:47.810
And more recently,
we have smartphones

00:02:47.810 --> 00:02:49.810
that are putting those
games right in our pocket

00:02:49.810 --> 00:02:51.934
and connecting us with
everybody else in the world.

00:02:51.934 --> 00:02:54.552
And those are just
a few examples.

00:02:54.552 --> 00:02:56.760
The games industry now is
bigger than it's ever been.

00:02:56.760 --> 00:03:01.970
This is a picture of the GDC up
in San Francisco from a Google

00:03:01.970 --> 00:03:03.680
session there this year.

00:03:03.680 --> 00:03:07.615
We had more people there,
I think, than even fit

00:03:07.615 --> 00:03:08.240
into this room.

00:03:08.240 --> 00:03:10.010
But right in this
room alone, we've

00:03:10.010 --> 00:03:11.927
got almost double
the amount of people

00:03:11.927 --> 00:03:13.510
that were at the
first Game Developers

00:03:13.510 --> 00:03:19.440
Conference I went to, the entire
conference, back 30 years ago.

00:03:19.440 --> 00:03:23.660
The games industry has grown
200-fold since then-- sorry,

00:03:23.660 --> 00:03:27.080
the GDC has grown 200-fold since
then-- and with good reason.

00:03:27.080 --> 00:03:29.980
Because there are all these
wonderful new technologies--

00:03:29.980 --> 00:03:33.670
platforms beyond just the kind
of computers and the dedicated

00:03:33.670 --> 00:03:35.760
consoles that we're
used to, but of course,

00:03:35.760 --> 00:03:39.340
we've seen browser-based social
gaming, downloadable games,

00:03:39.340 --> 00:03:41.820
a lot of indie games coming
that way, and of course,

00:03:41.820 --> 00:03:43.600
mobile games of all types.

00:03:43.600 --> 00:03:45.030
In the last couple
of years, we've

00:03:45.030 --> 00:03:47.760
now started to look at
virtual reality and wearables.

00:03:47.760 --> 00:03:51.260
So it's given us all sorts
of wonderful opportunities.

00:03:51.260 --> 00:03:53.710
And here at Google, we
make all sorts of hardware,

00:03:53.710 --> 00:03:55.510
software, and
services that help you

00:03:55.510 --> 00:03:57.780
develop games, grow
your audiences,

00:03:57.780 --> 00:03:59.280
and earn some profits.

00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:01.680
So today, as we're talking
about some of those things,

00:04:01.680 --> 00:04:04.400
and in the next few days as
you hear from our other groups,

00:04:04.400 --> 00:04:06.160
I hope you think
about the advantages

00:04:06.160 --> 00:04:08.640
that you get when you combine
some of those services

00:04:08.640 --> 00:04:11.880
together to explore new areas--
just as those examples I

00:04:11.880 --> 00:04:14.390
mentioned, in the past, of
new things coming together

00:04:14.390 --> 00:04:16.750
like that-- to see
what kind of new games,

00:04:16.750 --> 00:04:20.390
or even new entire types of
games, that you can create.

00:04:20.390 --> 00:04:23.350
And the practical reasons for
the experimenting with this--

00:04:23.350 --> 00:04:25.510
there are a lot of
payoffs for you.

00:04:25.510 --> 00:04:28.660
It's really, I think, like going
through a secluded mountain

00:04:28.660 --> 00:04:29.600
pass.

00:04:29.600 --> 00:04:31.570
Maybe there'll be a dead
end on the other side.

00:04:31.570 --> 00:04:33.770
Maybe it'll open up
into a fertile valley.

00:04:33.770 --> 00:04:36.700
Maybe there's an entire new
continent of possibility.

00:04:36.700 --> 00:04:38.880
The smartphone games,
when they came out,

00:04:38.880 --> 00:04:40.120
are a whole new continent.

00:04:40.120 --> 00:04:42.410
It's just amazing how
big that's gotten.

00:04:42.410 --> 00:04:45.130
And I think that we have some
really great possibilities

00:04:45.130 --> 00:04:47.519
coming up in those areas too.

00:04:47.519 --> 00:04:49.060
One of the reasons
for doing that is,

00:04:49.060 --> 00:04:53.470
if you combine some new exciting
thing, like virtual reality,

00:04:53.470 --> 00:04:58.600
with something as big as the
billion-plus Android smartphone

00:04:58.600 --> 00:05:00.600
users, and make a
game that works well

00:05:00.600 --> 00:05:02.600
in both of those
fields, then you've

00:05:02.600 --> 00:05:04.840
got something that has
the appeal and the press

00:05:04.840 --> 00:05:07.480
attention of virtual
reality, but the huge market

00:05:07.480 --> 00:05:09.340
of the existing
smartphones out there.

00:05:09.340 --> 00:05:11.210
And it's not easy to
do that sort of thing,

00:05:11.210 --> 00:05:13.850
but it's certainly
possible, and the payoff

00:05:13.850 --> 00:05:15.030
is really worthwhile.

00:05:15.030 --> 00:05:17.397
So that's just using some
existing technologies.

